---

<div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
  <!-- Header -->
  <div class="text-center mb-16">
    <h2 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-black text-gray-900 mb-4">
      Website Design FAQs
    </h2>
    <p class="text-lg md:text-xl text-gray-600 max-w-2xl mx-auto">
      Common questions about our website design and development services
    </p>
  </div>

  <!-- FAQ Grid - Two Independent Columns (Desktop only) -->
  <div class="grid grid-cols-1 lg:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
    
    <!-- Left Column -->
    <div class="space-y-6">
      <div class="bg-white border border-gray-200 rounded-lg shadow-2xl overflow-hidden">
        <button 
          class="faq-toggle-left w-full p-6 flex items-start gap-4 hover:bg-gray-50 transition text-left" 
          data-faq="web-faq1"
        >
          <div class="flex-1">
            <h3 class="text-lg font-bold text-gray-900">How long does a website take to build?</h3>
          </div>
          <svg 
            xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" 
            viewBox="0 0 24 24" 
            fill="none" 
            stroke="currentColor" 
            stroke-width="2" 
            class="faq-icon w-5 h-5 text-gray-400 flex-shrink-0 mt-1 transition-transform duration-300"
          >
            <polyline points="6 9 12 15 18 9"></polyline>
          </svg>
        </button>
        <div class="faq-content hidden px-6 pb-6">
          <p class="text-gray-600">On our Lightning platform, most websites are completed in approximately two weeks, depending on scope and complexity. WordPress builds typically take three to four weeks, as they require additional configuration and testing. We'll provide a specific timeline during your initial consultation.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-white border border-gray-200 rounded-lg shadow-2xl overflow-hidden">
        <button 
          class="faq-toggle-left w-full p-6 flex items-start gap-4 hover:bg-gray-50 transition text-left" 
          data-faq="web-faq3"
        >
          <div class="flex-1">
            <h3 class="text-lg font-bold text-gray-900">Can I work on my own website?</h3>
          </div>
          <svg 
            xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" 
            viewBox="0 0 24 24" 
            fill="none" 
            stroke="currentColor" 
            stroke-width="2" 
            class="faq-icon w-5 h-5 text-gray-400 flex-shrink-0 mt-1 transition-transform duration-300"
          >
            <polyline points="6 9 12 15 18 9"></polyline>
          </svg>
        </button>
        <div class="faq-content hidden px-6 pb-6">
          <p class="text-gray-600">We advise against self-editing your website. Similar to how you wouldn't re-roof your own home, website development requires specialized skills. On WordPress, we install a page builder to simplify updates, but this trades performance for convenience. Our Lightning platform handles updates through our team to maintain speed and security.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-white border border-gray-200 rounded-lg shadow-2xl overflow-hidden">
        <button 
          class="faq-toggle-left w-full p-6 flex items-start gap-4 hover:bg-gray-50 transition text-left" 
          data-faq="web-faq5"
        >
          <div class="flex-1">
            <h3 class="text-lg font-bold text-gray-900">What happens to my site if I leave?</h3>
          </div>
          <svg 
            xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" 
            viewBox="0 0 24 24" 
            fill="none" 
            stroke="currentColor" 
            stroke-width="2" 
            class="faq-icon w-5 h-5 text-gray-400 flex-shrink-0 mt-1 transition-transform duration-300"
          >
            <polyline points="6 9 12 15 18 9"></polyline>
          </svg>
        </button>
        <div class="faq-content hidden px-6 pb-6">
          <p class="text-gray-600">You're never locked in. If you leave, you can continue hosting with us at a low monthly cost. Lightning platform sites cannot be transferred—they'd need to be rebuilt on another platform of your choice. WordPress sites can be migrated away easily, though you'll need to renew any builder licenses separately.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-white border border-gray-200 rounded-lg shadow-2xl overflow-hidden">
        <button 
          class="faq-toggle-left w-full p-6 flex items-start gap-4 hover:bg-gray-50 transition text-left" 
          data-faq="web-faq7"
        >
          <div class="flex-1">
            <h3 class="text-lg font-bold text-gray-900">What if my website gets hacked?</h3>
          </div>
          <svg 
            xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" 
            viewBox="0 0 24 24" 
            fill="none" 
            stroke="currentColor" 
            stroke-width="2" 
            class="faq-icon w-5 h-5 text-gray-400 flex-shrink-0 mt-1 transition-transform duration-300"
          >
            <polyline points="6 9 12 15 18 9"></polyline>
          </svg>
        </button>
        <div class="faq-content hidden px-6 pb-6">
          <p class="text-gray-600">Lightning platform websites are extremely resistant to hacking since they lack the security vulnerabilities introduced by traditional updates. With WordPress, we can attempt restoration or cleaning, but severe breaches often require specialized security firms like Sucuri. Prevention through our Lightning platform is the best protection.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Right Column -->
    <div class="space-y-6">
      <div class="bg-white border border-gray-200 rounded-lg shadow-2xl overflow-hidden">
        <button 
          class="faq-toggle-right w-full p-6 flex items-start gap-4 hover:bg-gray-50 transition text-left" 
          data-faq="web-faq2"
        >
          <div class="flex-1">
            <h3 class="text-lg font-bold text-gray-900">I already have a website. Can you update it?</h3>
          </div>
          <svg 
            xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" 
            viewBox="0 0 24 24" 
            fill="none" 
            stroke="currentColor" 
            stroke-width="2" 
            class="faq-icon w-5 h-5 text-gray-400 flex-shrink-0 mt-1 transition-transform duration-300"
          >
            <polyline points="6 9 12 15 18 9"></polyline>
          </svg>
        </button>
        <div class="faq-content hidden px-6 pb-6">
          <p class="text-gray-600">If it's WordPress, we can likely update it depending on how it was originally built—though you'll still be working with a database-heavy platform. If speed is your priority, we recommend rebuilding on our Lightning platform, which delivers significantly faster performance and better conversion rates.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-white border border-gray-200 rounded-lg shadow-2xl overflow-hidden">
        <button 
          class="faq-toggle-right w-full p-6 flex items-start gap-4 hover:bg-gray-50 transition text-left" 
          data-faq="web-faq4"
        >
          <div class="flex-1">
            <h3 class="text-lg font-bold text-gray-900">Can I add my own content to the website?</h3>
          </div>
          <svg 
            xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" 
            viewBox="0 0 24 24" 
            fill="none" 
            stroke="currentColor" 
            stroke-width="2" 
            class="faq-icon w-5 h-5 text-gray-400 flex-shrink-0 mt-1 transition-transform duration-300"
          >
            <polyline points="6 9 12 15 18 9"></polyline>
          </svg>
        </button>
        <div class="faq-content hidden px-6 pb-6">
          <p class="text-gray-600">Absolutely. If you have content rights, just send us your text, images, and a description of placement. Our designers will implement it for you. For active marketing clients, content updates are included in your service package.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-white border border-gray-200 rounded-lg shadow-2xl overflow-hidden">
        <button 
          class="faq-toggle-right w-full p-6 flex items-start gap-4 hover:bg-gray-50 transition text-left" 
          data-faq="web-faq6"
        >
          <div class="flex-1">
            <h3 class="text-lg font-bold text-gray-900">Will my website work on mobile devices?</h3>
          </div>
          <svg 
            xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" 
            viewBox="0 0 24 24" 
            fill="none" 
            stroke="currentColor" 
            stroke-width="2" 
            class="faq-icon w-5 h-5 text-gray-400 flex-shrink-0 mt-1 transition-transform duration-300"
          >
            <polyline points="6 9 12 15 18 9"></polyline>
          </svg>
        </button>
        <div class="faq-content hidden px-6 pb-6">
          <p class="text-gray-600">Every website we build is fully responsive and optimized for mobile. Over 60% of web traffic comes from mobile devices, so we design mobile-first. All our sites look and perform beautifully on phones, tablets, and desktops.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-white border border-gray-200 rounded-lg shadow-2xl overflow-hidden">
        <button 
          class="faq-toggle-right w-full p-6 flex items-start gap-4 hover:bg-gray-50 transition text-left" 
          data-faq="web-faq8"
        >
          <div class="flex-1">
            <h3 class="text-lg font-bold text-gray-900">Do you provide ongoing maintenance and support?</h3>
          </div>
          <svg 
            xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" 
            viewBox="0 0 24 24" 
            fill="none" 
            stroke="currentColor" 
            stroke-width="2" 
            class="faq-icon w-5 h-5 text-gray-400 flex-shrink-0 mt-1 transition-transform duration-300"
          >
            <polyline points="6 9 12 15 18 9"></polyline>
          </svg>
        </button>
        <div class="faq-content hidden px-6 pb-6">
          <p class="text-gray-600">Yes. We offer maintenance packages that include regular updates, security monitoring, performance optimization, and technical support. For Lightning platform sites, maintenance is minimal since there are fewer moving parts. WordPress sites require more regular upkeep, which we handle for you.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

  </div>
</div>

<script is:inline>
  // Ensure all FAQs start hidden on page load
  window.addEventListener('DOMContentLoaded', function() {
    document.querySelectorAll('.faq-content').forEach(content => {
      content.classList.add('hidden');
    });
  });

  // LEFT COLUMN - Independent accordion
  document.querySelectorAll('.faq-toggle-left').forEach(button => {
    button.addEventListener('click', function(e) {
      e.preventDefault();
      const card = this.closest('.bg-white');
      const content = card.querySelector('.faq-content');
      const icon = this.querySelector('.faq-icon');
      
      // Close all OTHER FAQs in LEFT column only
      document.querySelectorAll('.faq-toggle-left').forEach(otherButton => {
        if (otherButton !== this) {
          const otherCard = otherButton.closest('.bg-white');
          const otherContent = otherCard.querySelector('.faq-content');
          const otherIcon = otherButton.querySelector('.faq-icon');
          otherContent.classList.add('hidden');
          otherIcon.classList.remove('rotate-180');
        }
      });
      
      // Toggle current FAQ
      content.classList.toggle('hidden');
      icon.classList.toggle('rotate-180');
    });
  });

  // RIGHT COLUMN - Independent accordion
  document.querySelectorAll('.faq-toggle-right').forEach(button => {
    button.addEventListener('click', function(e) {
      e.preventDefault();
      const card = this.closest('.bg-white');
      const content = card.querySelector('.faq-content');
      const icon = this.querySelector('.faq-icon');
      
      // Close all OTHER FAQs in RIGHT column only
      document.querySelectorAll('.faq-toggle-right').forEach(otherButton => {
        if (otherButton !== this) {
          const otherCard = otherButton.closest('.bg-white');
          const otherContent = otherCard.querySelector('.faq-content');
          const otherIcon = otherButton.querySelector('.faq-icon');
          otherContent.classList.add('hidden');
          otherIcon.classList.remove('rotate-180');
        }
      });
      
      // Toggle current FAQ
      content.classList.toggle('hidden');
      icon.classList.toggle('rotate-180');
    });
  });
</script>